participating-org.narrative:
Created in March 2018 as a Non Governmental Organization legally registered in Niger, New Challenges is a women's organization whose mission is to accompany and supervise women and girls on the whole of the Nigerian territory to be developed. not only their leadership through the transformation of skills and capacity building but also in the protection and promotion of their rights and duties.
 Led by a national coordinator elected in plenary by the general assembly and all the other members of the national executive board, the NGO New Challenges is strictly composed of young girls / women whose dynamism is well known beyond beyond our borders and works in perfect collaboration with men willing to invest in the smooth running of the structure. The curriculum and experience of the founding members in both NGOs and associations is one of the main strengths of this young organization.
In terms of affiliation, theNGO New Challenges is at the national level member of several youth and human rights structures, namely:
The National Youth Council;
Youth Collaborative Framework;
CONGAFEN;
The Young Entrepreneurs Association ...
And at the international level, she is a member of:
The Great YALI Family;
Moremie initiative for women leadership in Africa;
  The Network of Women Leaders of West Africa
